<statement>
<p>A triangle has sides with lengths <m>\displaystyle{a}={7.00}</m>, <m>\displaystyle{b}={7.49}</m>, and <m>\displaystyle{c}={8.83}</m>. Calculate all of the angles of this triangle.</p>
<p>A=<fillin characters="4" /> (across from side of length <m>\displaystyle{a}={7.00}</m>)</p>
<p>
  B=<fillin characters="4" /> (across from side of length <m>\displaystyle{b}={7.49}</m>)</p>
<p>
  C=<fillin characters="4" /> (across from side of length <m>\displaystyle{c}={8.83}</m>)</p>
<p>Round to two decimal places.</p>


</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li>49.97</li><li>55.02</li><li>77.32</li></ul></p><p>Because we have all three sides, we can use the law of cosines for the first angle.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{7}^{{2}}={7.49}^{{2}}+{8.83}^{{2}}-{2}{\left({7.49}\right)}{\left({8.83}\right)}{\cos{{\left({A}\right)}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{49}={56.1001}+{77.9689}-{132.2734}{\cos{{\left({A}\right)}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{85.069}=-{132.2734}{\cos{{\left({A}\right)}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{0.6431300624313}={\cos{{\left({A}\right)}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{A}={49.974381670411}={49.97}</m>.</p>
<p>For a second angle, we can use the shorter law of sines.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle\frac{{\sin{{\left({49.974381670411}\right)}}}}{{7.00}}=\frac{{\sin{{\left({B}\right)}}}}{{7.49}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{0.30709735525343}={\sin{{\left({B}\right)}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{B}={\arcsin{{\left(-{0.30709735525343}\right)}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{B}={55.020773316355}\approx{55.02}</m></p>
<p>The third angle we can calculate using the angle sum property.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{49.974381670411}+{55.020773316355}+{C}={180}^{\circ}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{C}={77.321943182653}\approx{77.32}</m></p>

</solution>
</myopenmath>

